The article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney. Carney discusses President Obama's upcoming speech in Nashua, New Hampshire, where he will discuss his approach to energy security. Carney mentions that the President will talk about increasing fossil fuel production, reducing dependency on foreign imports, diversifying energy sources, and investing in alternative energy. Carney also addresses questions about the President's proposal to remove subsidies for oil and gas companies, the situation in Afghanistan, oil prices, and the President's reelection campaign.